                  <handDesc><handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic"><seg type="rubrication"><foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign><foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢየሱስ፡</foreign></seg></handNote></handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#ir" facs="001">Fol. ir</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/>, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiiv" facs="004">Fol. iiiv</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> with two <term key="angel" ana="#angel"/>, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#24r" facs="027">Fol. 24r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref> with <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5695John">John</persName> standing beside the cross, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#43v" facs="047">Fol. 43v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref>, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#44v" facs="048">Fol. 44v</locus><desc>Geometric patterns <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1109GeometricPatterns"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1109GeometricPatterns</span></ref>, reminiscent of the evil eye, painted over text</desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d6">
                    Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r" facs="004">fols. 1r, </locus>, ornamental band;
                    <locus target="#28r" facs="031">28r, </locus>, lines of black dots;
                    <locus target="#43r" facs="046">43r, </locus>, multiple full stops and a line of black dots;
                    <locus target="#44r" facs="047">44r</locus>, multiple full stops</decoNote>
                </decoDesc>
                <additions><list>
                  <item xml:id="a1"><desc type="GuestText" xml:lang="am"><locus target="#iv #iir #iiv #iiir" facs="002 003">Fols. iv, iir, iiv, iiir</locus> excerpt <q>On the Faith of the Orthodox Church</q>, in Amharic. Possibly related to <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1584Hayman">Hāymānot
                                                  rǝtǝʿǝt</ref>. The first folio and last folios of text have been painted over.</desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="a2"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#43r" facs="046">Fol. 43r</locus>Mentions the owner, Wäldä Giyorgis (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡</foreign>)</desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="a3"><desc type="GuestText" xml:lang="gez"><locus target="#44r" facs="047">Fol. 44r</locus>Unidentified text in Amharic. Incomplete at the beginning</desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="a4"><desc xml:lang="ti"><locus target="#44r" facs="047">Fol. 44r</locus> note in Tigreñña </desc></item>
                  <item xml:id="e1"><desc>Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly <locus target="#4v #7r #10r #10v #12r" facs="008 010 013 014 015">folss. 4v, 7r, 10r, 10v, 12r, </locus>, etc.;
                    and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted <locus target="#36r" facs="039">36r, </locus>;
                    text has been removed <locus target="#2r #2v #3r #3v #4r" facs="005 005 007">2r, 2v, 3r, 3v, 4r</locus>, etc.</desc></item>
</list></additions>

